theorem Topology.interior_closure_eq_univ_iff_closure_eq_univ
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior (closure A) = (Set.univ : Set X) ↔
      closure A = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
  constructor
  · intro hInt
    -- Show `closure A` contains every point.
    have h_sub : (Set.univ : Set X) ⊆ closure A := by
      intro x _
      have hxInt : (x : X) ∈ interior (closure A) := by
        -- Rewrite using `hInt`.
        simpa [hInt] using (by
          have : (x : X) ∈ (Set.univ : Set X) := by simp
          exact this)
      exact interior_subset hxInt
    -- Combine the two inclusions to obtain the desired equality.
    exact Set.Subset.antisymm (Set.Subset_univ _) h_sub
  · intro hCl
    -- The forward implication is supplied by an existing lemma.
    exact
      Topology.interior_closure_eq_univ_of_dense (X := X) (A := A) hCl
